Class IpcLogEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.netflix.spectator.ipc.IpcLogEntry

  • public final class IpcLogEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    Builder used to fill in and submit a log entry associated with an IPC request.

      • withLogLevel

        public IpcLogEntry withLogLevel(org.slf4j.event.Level level)
        Set the log level to use when sending to SLF4j. The default level is DEBUG. For high volume use-cases it is recommended to set the level to TRACE to avoid excessive logging.

      • withLatency

        public IpcLogEntry withLatency(long latency,
                               java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
        Set the latency for the request. This will typically be set automatically using markStart() and markEnd(). Use this method if the latency value is provided by the implementation rather than measured using this entry.

      • markStart

        public IpcLogEntry markStart()
        Record the starting time for the request and update the number of inflight requests. This should be called just before starting the execution of the request. As soon as the request completes it is recommended to call markEnd().

      • markEnd

        public IpcLogEntry markEnd()
        Record the latency for the request based on the completion time. This will be implicitly called when the request is logged, but it is advisable to call as soon as the response is received to minimize the amount of response processing that is counted as part of the request latency.

        public IpcLogEntry withOwner(java.lang.String owner)

      • addTag

        public IpcLogEntry addTag(com.netflix.spectator.api.Tag tag)
        Add custom tags to the request metrics. Note, IPC metrics already have many tags and it is not recommended for users to tack on additional context. In particular, any additional tags should have a guaranteed low cardinality. If additional tagging causes these metrics to exceed limits, then you may lose all visibility into requests.

      • addTag

        public IpcLogEntry addTag(java.lang.String k,
                          java.lang.String v)
        Add custom tags to the request metrics. Note, IPC metrics already have many tags and it is not recommended for users to tack on additional context. In particular, any additional tags should have a guaranteed low cardinality. If additional tagging causes these metrics to exceed limits, then you may lose all visibility into requests.

      • log

        public void log()
        Log the request. This entry will potentially be reused after this is called. The user should not attempt any further modifications to the state of this entry.
